reviews.text: This station has all the aesthetic charm of a brick being stapled to a fire extinguisher; except taller.

Let's be honest, this station needs flattening. It has a strange little doorway off the street that is always flanked by resident beggars. There's a little concrete shelter to help you get out of the rain and into the puddles... and they're always suspiciously yellow! Given its small size, the lack of financial investment is a travesty, it wouldn't take much. On the plus side, the overgrown banks are home to some lovely birds.

Operator in office seemed upset I disturbed him to purchase a ticket. Waiting area has flies buzzing around, perhaps due to bins being full or cans of liquid left lying on floor. Clear information board and disabled access to both sides as a positive. Some areas to shelter if its raining. Station recently received a new lick of paint.
